By: Thomas Traherne
---
For in the Kingdom of Glory it is impossible to fall. No man can sin that
clearly seeth the beauty of God’s face： because no man can sin against
his own happiness, that is, none can when he sees it clearly, willingly,
and wittingly forsake it, tempter, temptation, loss, and danger being all seen.
